desc.en: 16 of the world's best CS:GO teams will attend the group stage of ESL One Cologne 2018 but only the very best will make it to the LANXESS arena. Here we have crowned new legends, watched the underdog defeat the fan's favorite and witnessed the best teams fall only to rise again. Year after year ESL One Cologne has seen trophies lifted and tears being shed by players and fans alike.

World of Esports is the place to catch up on the latest and best from the world of esports. From CS:GO, to League of Legends and Rocket League, EsportsCenter brings news, interviews, plays of the week and much more in this brand new show, which aims to provide exceptional insight into the world of competitive gaming. Featuring host OJ Borg.

Get ready for all the best of this year HGC NA Fall Regional. This season has seen top names fade into the background as new teams stepped up with confidence. See Murloc Geniuses, Naventic, Denial, Astral Authority, Team Name Change, Guldans Game, Gale Force and Vox Nihill in action.

desc.en: With the Heroes of the Storm Summer Regional right here you can relive the best of the best.

Eight teams from around the world gathered in Katowice, Poland in order to fight for their share of a minimum 100.000 dollars prize pool as well as the prestigious title and trophy, and none of them were willing to give up their chance without a fight. This game is between CLG and SKT T1.

This match-up is between Qiao Gu Reapers and Fnatic.

The first official competitive Dragon Ball FighterZ-tournament ever will take place at Gamescom in Cologne running from August 23rd-26th. Here a new enhanced playable demo-version of the upcoming Dragon Ball-game will be presented, and the tournament is played on the 25th of August.

DOTA 2 ESL One is back this time from Hamburg. It is the eighth time and ESL's first ever event in the Barclaycard Arena of Hamburg. Only the best teams are ready to compete in the ESL One Hamburg, where the prestigious prize pool is $1,000,000 USD
